FR940503-2-00167 FR940503-2-00103 Tuesday May 3, 1994 Part VI Department of Education Fund for Innovation in Education: Innovation in Education Program_Partnerships for Standards-Based Professional Development of K&hyph;12 Educators; Notice of Final Priority for Fiscal Years 1994 and 1995 Federal Register ␣/␣Vol. 59, No. 84␣/␣Tuesday, May 3, 1994␣/␣Notices DEPARTMENT OF EDUCATION Fund for Innovation in Education: Innovation in Education Program_Partnerships for Standards-Based Professional Development of K&hyph;12 Educators AGENCY: Department of Education. ACTION: Notice of final priority for fiscal years 1994 and 1995. SUMMARY: The Secretary announces an absolute priority for fiscal years 1994 and 1995 under the Fund for Innovation in Education (FIE): Innovation in Education Program to support innovative projects that provide K&hyph;12 teachers and other educators with sustained, high quality professional development opportunities that are aligned with challenging content and professional standards developed at the national, State or local levels. The intent of this priority is to enable school educators, working with appropriate university, community, and business partners, to create and maintain model learning environments that will help all students in elementary and secondary schools achieve challenging academic standards in subjects such as English, mathematics, science, history, geography, civics, foreign languages, economics, and the arts. EFFECTIVE DATE: This priority takes effect either 45 days after publication in the Federal Register or later if the Congress takes certain adjournments. If you want to know the effective date of this priority, call or write the Department of Education contact person.
